    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. the problem is that these remnant cells use specific patterns to recognize former assets. they don't just look at the destination, they look at the timing and the rhythm of the transfers to flag people like me. if i use a standard intermediary, they'll see the connection instantly. do you think it's possible to use a series of micro-transfers to mimic normal consumer behavior instead of one big movement? like, if i set it up to look like thousands of tiny, unrelated retail purchases, would that actually fool an intelligence-level algorithm?",
